 in modern Mexico. The author examines responses to suicide and death and disproves the long-held belief that Mexicans possess a cavalier attitude toward suffering.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aDeathxSocial aspectszMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aMurderzMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 0aSuicidezMexicoxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Mexico.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aalcoholism.  aautopsy.  acivilization.  acrime.  acriminal investigation.  aculture.  adanger.  adepression.  aemotions.  aepidemic.  agrief.  ahard times.  ahealth and wellness.  ahomicide.  alatin america.  alatin american history.  alaw.  alegal.  alife and death.  aloss.  amental health.  amexico city.  amodern world.  amodernization.  amourning.  amurder.  apublic health.  apublic space.  asocial class.  asuffering.  asuicidal ideation.  asuicide.  atragedy.  aviolence.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052029032740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964532/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY